text: Moraya Wilson (born 10 September 2001) is an Australian model and beauty pageant titleholder who was crowned Miss Universe Australia 2023. She will represent Australia at the Miss Universe 2023 competition in San Salvador, El Salvador. == Biography == Wilson was born in Melbourne. She started working at Caulfield Grammar School as a sports coach across three disciplines namely athletics, cross country and snowsports. In November 2018, Wilson joined Vivien’s Model Management in Melbourne as a model. Wilson entered and graduate from RMIT University with a bachelor’s degree in business marketing. == Pageantry == On September 1, 2023, Wilson competed against 23 other Miss Universe Australia 2023 finalists at the Sofitel Melbourne on Collins in Melbourne, she won the title and was succeeded by Monique Riley. On November 18, 2023, Wilson will represent Australia at Miss Universe 2023 in San Salvador, El Salvador. ==References== ==Other websites== *Moraya Wilson - Vivien's Models * Category:Beauty pageant winners Category:2001 births Category:Living people Category:Australian people Category:Australian models
